üéØ Project Overview

Omega Nutrici√≥n API Platform is a Microservices-based system dedicated
to managing the end-to-end lifecycle of supplement and packaged food production, from raw material procurement to final order
fulfillment.

This platform is structured into three highly independent services, each managing its own data store to ensure
scalability and resilience.

üèóÔ∏è Architecture and Service Breakdown

The system is composed of three core microservices, each built with FastAPI and operating asynchronously.
They communicate over HTTP APIs rather than sharing a single database.


| Service | Primary Domain | Data Ownership  | API Documentation |
| ------- | -------------- | --------------- | ----------------- |
| **1. Production** | Manufacturing and Inputs | Suppliers, Raw Materials, Formulas, Batches, and Quality Control.| http://localhost:8002/docs |
| **2. StockInventory** | ManagementCurrent Stock Levels |(Products, Materials, Packaging), Warehouse Locations, and Inventory Movements. |http://localhost:8001/docs |
| **3. AccountSales and Customers**|Customer Records, Orders, Payments |Invoicing, and Balance Tracking. |http://localhost:8000/docs |

üíª Tech Stack

| Component | Technology | Rationale |
| --------- | ---------- | --------- |
| API Framework | Python (3.11+) and FastAPI | High-performance, async-native, and automatic OpenAPI documentation.|
| Data Validation | Pydantic | Enforces clear, consistent data schemas across all service communication.|
| Databases | PostgresSQL (per service) | Reliable, transactional data storage for independent service data. |
| Containerization | Docker & Docker Compose | Ensures reproducible and isolated environments for local development. |
| Inter-service HTTP | httpxAsynchronous |HTTP client for non-blocking communication between services. |

üöÄ Getting Started (Local Development)

This project requires GitHub to be installed.

1. Clone the Repository:
**Bash:**
git clone https://github.com/ingega/omeganutricion.git
cd omega_nutricion
2. creates a .venv
**Bash:**
python -m venv .venv  # any name you want
3. Activate your .venv
**Bash:**
source .venv/bin/activate
4. create a .env file in root folder
**Bash:**
touch .env
5. Create a random secret key
**Bash:**
openssl rand -hex 32
open your .env file and add this two lines:
SECRET_KEY = # paste the output of your console here
ALGORITHM="HS256"

6. Run your project
Bash:
uvicorn src.services.products.endpoints.main:app --reload --port 8000  # for production microservice
uvicorn src.services.stocks.endpoints.main:app --reload --port 8001  # for stocks microservice
uvicorn src.services.customers.endpoints.main:app --reload --port 8002  # for customer microservice
**Run every service in a different window**
Once all services are running, you can interact with the documentation via your browser:
Account Service (Port 8000): http://localhost:8000/docs
Stock Service (Port 8001): http://localhost:8001/docs
Production Service (Port 8002): http://localhost:8002/docs

